9:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Amazon CodeWhisperer (Q Developer) and Codium AI share a solid foundation of core features including Code Review, Debugging, Multi Language, Ide Integration. Where Amazon CodeWhisperer (Q Developer) pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Autocomplete and Code Generation and Refactoring and Chat and Documentation, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Codium AI uniquely offers Test Generation, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Amazon CodeWhisperer (Q Developer) holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while Codium AI scores 7/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
a:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both platforms start at similar price points ($19/mo). Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Amazon CodeWhisperer (Q Developer)'s free tier and Codium AI's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
